 set designs, and shooting scripts. Rounding out the book are continuity Polaroids used during filming and photographs taken on the set by Bill Wittliff, which place you behind the scenes in the middle of the action. Designed as a companion for A Book of Photographs from Lonesome Dove, Wittliff’s magnificent fine art volume, A Book on the Making of Lonesome Dove is a must-have for every fan of this American epic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aTelevision actors and actressesvInterviews. 0aTelevision actors and actressesxInterviews. 0aTelevision producers and directorsvInterviews. 0aTelevision producers and directorsxInterviews. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh1 aWilson, Jeff.1 aWittliff, Bill.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311074534440uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/73584240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292739482423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292739482/original  a978-3-11-074534-4  University of Texas Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK